<DOC><DOCNO> AP891124-0084 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-11-24-89 1222EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Pakistan-Bomb     11-24 0145</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Pakistan-Bomb,0149</SECOND><HEAD>3 Palestinians Killed In Bomb Explosion</HEAD><DATELINE>PESHAWAR, Pakistan (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A remote-controlled bomb exploded inthis frontier city Friday, killing three Palestinians returningfrom an afternoon prayer service.   Sheik Abdullah Al Assam and his two sons, Ebrahim, 23, andAdnan, 15, reportedly were embroiled in Afghanistan's brutaldecade-old war, fighting on the side of anti-communist guerrillas,police said. They had lived in Pakistan for 15 months.   Al Assam recruited nationals from Arab countries to fight withU.S.-backed guerrillas to protect their Moslem faith, policesources said.   The bomb, planted in a roadside ditch, was detonated when AlAssam's car passed by, police said. No one has claimedresponsibility.   In recent years, hundreds of bombs have exploded in Pakistan'sNorthwest Frontier Province, where the majority of an estimated 3.5million Afghan war refugees in Pakistan live. Another 2 millionrefugees live in Iran.</TEXT></DOC>